life, art and culture of our country. If it is true that between food and art there is an elective affinity, we can be food artists too using the right ingredients. Our handmade Pasta is especially made for those who want to serve every day a masterpiece of the Mediterranean Diet.\n\n<em>Spaghetti, 500gr (17.64oz), </em>\n\nIngredients: durum semolina, water. One of the most popular Italian dishes around the world. Thanks to their shape, versatility and inimitable taste, Spaghetti are used as the basis for many recipes and represent a true emblem of Italian gastronomy.\n\n<em>Fusilli, 500gr (17.64oz), </em>\n\nIngredients: durum semolina, water. Fusilli belong to the Italian culinary tradition. Thanks to their long, spiraled shape Fusilli can be topped with any sauce and hold any dressing at its best. They are usually served combined with traditional sauces such as tomato sauces with meat and vegetables. Fusilli can also be broken in half and added to soups, turned into a beautiful salad or baked in casseroles.\n\n<em>Lumache, 500gr (17.64oz), </em>\n\nIngredients: durum semolina, water. Lumache, literally “Snails”, are a kind of pasta typical of the regions Campania and Liguria. Lumache add an ancient taste to any dish with their distinctive shape and match well with vegetable-based sauces such as mushroom, artichoke and pepper sauce. Thanks to their peculiar shape, they are also suited to be stuffed with fillings of any kind.\n\n<em>Linguine, 500gr (17.64oz), </em>\n\nIngredients: durum semolina, water. Linguine, literally “Little Tongues”, are long and flat pasta, which has a great shape to complement a variety of sauces. It is best suited for fish and seafood sauces, in particular clams and mussels, which are very widespread throughout Italy. They are also a good choice for salads and stir-fry dishes.\n\n<strong>SEASONING </strong>\n\n<em>Extra virgin olive oil, 250ml (8.45 fl. oz). </em>\n\nCultivar: Rotondella, Leccino, Frantoiano, Pendolino, Carpellese. Energizing food rich in antioxidants and anti-inflammatory substances, such as monounsaturated and polyunsaturated fat acids, B-carotene, phytosterols and polyphenols, which give it a delicate but persistent taste with a slightly bitter aftertaste. Obtained through a scrupulous production process that preserves its unique features and ensures the acidity does not exceed 0,3%. After picking, olives are stored and preserved in appropriate ventilated containers away from heat sources. Pressing takes place within 24 – 48 hours using the antique method of cold crushing and light pressing, carried out through mechanical processes only without using any chemical processes or substances.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Balsamic Vinegar of Modena IGP, 250ml (8.45 fl. oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: cooked grape must, wine vinegar. The great success of the Balsamic Vinegar of Modena derives from its unrivalled quality as well as from its versatility and adaptability to different kinds of cooking and to the most varied ingredients. It is a condiment widely used in our gastronomic scene since it gives dishes a sharper, pleasant and persistent taste. You can dress various courses, both sweet and salty, with our Balsamic Vinegar of Modena IGP and the result will always be tasty and of the highest quality. Its authenticity and high organoleptic characteristics witness that it is a 100 % natural product, free from colorings, thickening agents, additives or caramel.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Pearls with Balsamic Vinegar of Modena IGP, 50gr (1.76oz) </em>\n\nIngredients: cooked grape must, wine vinegar, balsamic Vinegar of Modena (Cooked grape must, Wine vinegar 10%), water. Thickener: cellulose gum, gelling agents: calcium chloride, sodium alginate. Contains sulfites. Pearls are small spheres similar to caviar, with a soft consistency, filled with Modena Aromatic Vinegar IGP.A few Pearls of this delicious product give courses a balanced taste of sweet and sour flavour. Our Pearls represent an innovative way to serve a typical Italian product but in a renewed look. Their form has a strong and elegant impact, and they are perfect to set high-quality gastronomy off and to offer a unique cooking experience.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Semidry Basil, 30g (1.06oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: basil 87%, salt, vinegar, lactic acid, citric acid. Semi-dry Basil adds to every course the natural freshness and aroma of the herbs grown around the Mediterranean Sea. Basil is in fact a symbol of Mediterranean fragrances and an essential ingredient of traditional Italian cuisine. A simple pinch of Semi-dry Basil will enhance the flavor of every course and add to your pasta, pizza, pesto and many other courses the taste of real Italian cuisine. Our strict production standards keep unaltered its unique aroma and preserve the organoleptic properties and nutrients, such as potassium, iron, phosphorus, magnesium and vitamin A.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Semidry Rosemary, 30g (1.06oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: rosemary 87%, salt, vinegar, lactic acid, citric acid. Thanks to the special drying technique and the addition of a drop of extra-virgin olive oil, the aroma and taste of the rosemary remains unaltered, as if it were fresh. Undisputed protagonist of many typical courses, Rosemary is a symbol of Mediterranean tastes and fragrances and an essential ingredient of traditional Italian cuisine. Our strict production standards keep unaltered its unique aroma and preserve the organoleptic properties and nutrients such as flavonoids and tannins, which provide important anti-inflammatory and antibiotic benefits.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>TOMATOES </strong>\n\nMedeaterranean tomatoes are the very essence of quality and flavour. Through them, we have become accustomed to the real, genuine flavours of the past, and have learnt that simple food is also the best. Authenticity and flavour will always be the pillars of Medeaterranean philosophy and also the hallmarks of Italian food throughout the world. Therefore, we will always do our bit to get a genuine taste of Italy to the tables of those who love to eat well.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Red Datterini Tomatoes, 400g (14.11oz). </em>\n\nSmall red Datterini tomatoes grown in Italy, tomato juice, acidity regulator: citric acid. The Red Datterino Tomato is an irreplaceable symbol of the Italian culinary tradition. Characteristic for their sweetness and rich taste, Red Datterini tomatoes are perfect to prepare sauces in few minutes, excellent for a simple pasta sauce as well as to garnish vegetables, fish, meatballs and fresh cheese. &gt; Yellow Datterini Tomatoes, 400g (14.11oz). Small yellow Datterini tomatoes grown in Italy, tomato juice, acidity regulator: citric acid. The Yellow Datterino Tomato is an authentic Italian delicacy. Its juice is a great ingredient for the preparation of vegetable-based sauces and veloutés, exceptional when paired with yellow vegetables as carrots, pumpkin and yellow peppers, enhancing their color and sweetness. Its rich and intense taste makes it a perfect dressing for rice and pasta as well.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Peeled Tomatoes, 400g (14.11oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: peeled tomatoes, tomato juice, acidity regulator: citric acid. Made from Italy’s finest tomatoes and are always a classic for tomato based sauces. Bursting with flavor and color, they are a symbol of the Italian culinary tradition and are ideal for the preparation of tomato sauces for pasta, meat, poultry dishes and pizza. Our Peeled Tomatoes are packed in dense tasty juice to provide the perfect balance. They are 100% natural, free from artificial flavorings, colorings and preservatives. &gt; Tomatoe Pureé, 350g (12.35oz). Ingredients: tomatoes grown in Italy, acidity regulator: citric acid. Made using the finest and best ripe tomatoes grown in Italy. It is perfectly smooth and can be used as a basis for soups and sauces as well as a substitute for fresh tomatoes in all recipes. The rich and sweet flavor of our Purée brings to the table the genuine taste of homemade dishes inspired to the Italian traditional cooking.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>LEGUMES &amp; RICE </strong>\n\n<em>Carnaroli rice, 500g (17.64oz). </em>\n\nSuperfine Carnaroli is one of the best sorts of rice among the Italian rice varieties. The firm, short grains allow Carnaroli Rice to absorb huge amounts of liquid without overcooking, creating the luxurious, creamy texture that is the hallmark of a superior risotto. Carnaroli is the absolute protagonist of many traditional Italian recipes and one of the main ingredients of the Mediterranean Diet. Moreover, this quality of Rice has remarkable health properties: it is rich in potassium, magnesium and phosphorus, low in sodium, easily digestible and gluten-free.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Chickpeas, 500g (17.64oz). </em>\n\nMay contain traces of cereals with gluten, soya and lupin. Chickpeas are one of the most ancient legumes and are used as a basis for many Mediterranean dishes. Chickpeas are heart-healthy component of a balanced diet, being a good source of calcium, B Vitamins, protein and iron. The Chickpeas are of the highest quality and boost a unique taste and consistency. Our Chickpeas will bring to the table the passion for ancient tastes, combining authenticity, simplicity and tastiness.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCannellini Beans, 500g (17.64oz).\n\nMay contain traces of cereals with gluten, soya and lupin. Cannellini beans are heart-healthy component of a balanced diet and have a high nutritional value, thus providing a viable alternative to the consumption of animal proteins. They are rich in starch, fiber, protein and helpful in lowering cholesterol levels. Protagonists of many courses typical of our regions, Cannellini beans are a perfect example of the balance between “healthy” and “tasty” which makes Italian gastronomy so popular around the world.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Umbria Lentils, 500g (17.64oz). </em>\n\nMay contain traces of cereals with gluten, soya and lupin. Due to the rigid climatic conditions in which they grow, Umbria Lentils are the only legumes that do not need processing in order to be preserved. Umbria Lentils have a high nutritional value being a great source of protein, fiber, mineral salts and iron. They retain their shape when cooked and have a wonderful, nutty, earthy savor. Their typical thin and soft peel allows to cook them without presoaking, thus reducing the preparation time. In Italy, lentils are often cooked with pork, absorbing the meat’s flavors while balancing its richness.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>SEAFOOD </strong>\n\n<em>Anchovy Filets, 130g (4.6oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: anchovies, sunflower oil, salt. Anchovy Fillets are a typical food of Southern Italy, where they are used as the basis for many traditional recipes. The love for the sea has put the Mediterranean Sea at the core of our gastronomic culture with Southern Italy being the undisputed homeland of such tradition. Fished exclusively in the Mediterranean Sea, are hand cleaned and processed right after being caught in order to preserve their organoleptic and nutritional qualities. Their processing is carried out using traditional methods handed down from generation to generation. Among the health properties of our local anchovies is the high content in polyunsaturated fat acids, helpful in lowering cholesterol levels.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Cetara Anchovies extract, 100ml (3.38 fl. oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: salted anchovies extract, salt. The Anchovies Extract is a traditional fish-based sauce produced in Cetara, on the Amalfi Coast. This amber liquid, similar to the Ancient Roman garum, is made by aging anchovies in salt according to an old processing method, passed down by the Cetara fishermen from father to son. The Anchovies Extract is used mostly to season spaghetti, but also to flavor vegetables, seafood and fish dishes. Medeaterranean Anchovies Extract is a true delicacy and a very healthy condiment, easily digestible and rich in Vitamin A.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>BAKERY</strong>\n\n<em>Durum Wheat Friselle, 350gr (12.35oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: durum-wheat flour, water, sour dough starter, salt. The Friselle are a traditional bakery specialty of the region Apulia. Formerly used as bread by Crusaders or, in more recent times, by anglers and farmers, Friselle are ideal to whet your appetite creating tasty aperitifs. Italians traditionally dress them with oil, salt, chopped tomatoes and oregano. Produced with only few ingredients like the durum wheat flour, water and salt, to ensure their genuineness and high quality. Thanks to their crispness and simplicity, they will complement all dishes adding a taste of the fresh and local “frugal cooking”.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Taralli with extra Virgin Olive Oil, 250gr (8.82oz). </em>\n\nIngredients: wheat flour type “00”, white wine (contains sulphites), extra virgin olive oil 14%, olive oil 6%, salt. May contain traces of sesame seeds. The Taralli with Extra-virgin Olive Oil are a traditional bakery specialty of the region Apulia. Usually accompanied by a glass of wine, Taralli are the perfect appetizers for all occasions. Made with only few, selected ingredients, such as wheat flour, white wine and high quality Extra-virgin Olive Oil. The artisanal production process, carried out through traditional methods, guarantees the quality and authenticity of this delicious product.','Cupid & Psyche','A selection of the best Italian food products, declining for centuries the lifestyle of Mediterranean people. A real richness of our culture - not only for the unique taste of its food, but also for its contribution to health. GMO free, high quality, natural and 100% Italian food. Highest quality, carefully selected products, result of a sustainable agricultural production, respectful for nature and its cycles, that does not take advantage of over-exploitation of natural resources. Shipping included.','inherit','closed','closed','','2592-autosave-v1','','','2016-02-21 14:24:47','2016-02-21 14:24:47','',2592,'http://